When specifying a space blueprint in a plugin you can indicate that the Space home page should have child pages created under it by adding the template references for those pages inside the home page template reference, like so:

{code}
<content-template ref="hierarchy-blueprint-content-template">
    <content-template ref="hierarchy-child-a-content-template"/>
    <content-template ref="hierarchy-child-b-content-template"/>
</content-template>
{code}

(copied from the [hello-blueprint sample plugin|https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/hello-blueprint/src/master/src/main/resources/atlassian-plugin.xml])

If these nested templates can be declared for space blueprints, it should be possible to declare them for content blueprints.

